terms.medium_def:
A man living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.1.14; 
referred to as Deuel (דְּעוּאֵל), or Reuel (רְעוּאֵל); 
father of Eliasaph. § father of Eliasaph, the captain of the tribe of Gad at the time of the numbering of the people at Sinai, also called 'Reuel'

A priest from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at 1Ch.9.10; 
only referred to as Jedaiah (יְדַעְיָה); 
a son of Joiarib.

A man from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at 1Ch.7.6; 
only referred to as Jediael (יְדִיעֲאֵל); 
son of Benjamin; 
a brother of Bela, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ahiram, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, Ard and Ahiram; 
father of Bilhan.

A High Priest from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at Neh.12.11; 
only referred to as Jaddua (יַדּוּעַ); 
a son of Johanan.

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.2.28; 
only referred to as Jada (יָדָע); 
son of Onam; 
a brother of Shammai; 
father of Jether and Jonathan. § a Judahite, son of Onam and brother of Shammai, in the genealogy of the sons of Jerahmeel by his wife Atarah

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.11.45; 
only referred to as Jediael (יְדִיעֲאֵל); 
son of Shimri; 
a brother of Joha.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.26.2; 
only referred to as Jediael (יְדִיעֲאֵל); 
son of Meshelemiah; 
a brother of Zechariah, Zebadiah, Jathniel, Elam, Jehohanan and Eliehoenai.
